===================== HTML ===========================
<body>
    <nav>
        This is the navigation
    </nav>

    <h1>My Website</h1>

    <p>
        The text is this paragraph
        is completely irrelevant
    </p>
</body>
======================================================
====================== CSS ===========================
body {
    color: #444444;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-family: sans-serif;

    border-top: 10px solid #1098ad;
}
======================================================

~ body element is the parent element.


    color: #444444;
    font-size: 16px;
    font-family: sans-serif;
~ the three properties above is applied to <nav>, <h1>, and <p> content text,
  because those three properties are related to the text.
  ~ only the border doesn't get inherited.
~ Not all properties get inherited. It's mostly ones related to text:
  font-family, font-style, font-weight, font-size, color, line-height,
  letter-spacing, text-align, text-transform, text-shadow, list-style, etc.
